5|$|Before the {{beginning}} of the French Revolution in 1789 there were eight times as many <b>slaves</b> <b>in</b> <b>the</b> colony as there were white and mixed-race people put together. In 1789 the French were importing 30,000 slaves a year and there were half a million <b>slaves</b> <b>in</b> <b>the</b> French part of the island alone, compared to about 30,000 whites.|$|E
