50|$|Deplorable {{conditions}} for <b>the</b> thousands of <b>slaves</b> <b>in</b> Saint-Domingue, <b>the</b> most profitable <b>slave</b> colony <b>in</b> <b>the</b> world, {{led to the}} uprisings which would {{be known as the}} first successful <b>slave</b> revolt <b>in</b> <b>the</b> New World. Slavery <b>in</b> <b>the</b> French colonies was abolished by the Convention dominated by <b>the</b> Jacobins <b>in</b> 1794. However, Napoleon reinstated it in 1802. <b>In</b> 1804, <b>the</b> colony of Saint-Domingue became an independent state, the Republic of Haiti.|$|R
